Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil over high heat. When boiling, stir in the @red and black quinoa{50%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring back to the boil. Lower the heat and simmer until the quinoa has doubled in size and the seed has visibly split, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain into a #sieve{} and run under cold water to cool the quinoa. Once cooled, stand the sieve over the saucepan to drain fully.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2%tin} in a sieve. Put in a large #bowl{}. Trim the @spring onion{1} then thinly slice. Chop the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm chunks. Add the spring onion and tomatoes to the bowl, set aside. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Set aside. Pop the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and @ground cumin{2%tsp} in a large bowl. Use your hands to rub the flavours over the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the chicken and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, frequently until nicely browned and cooked through. This will take around ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the insides onto a #chopping board{}. Cut into 2cm chunks and add to the beans, onion and tomato in the bowl. Stir in the lime zest. Squeeze in the lime juice and season with salt and pepper.

When the quinoa is cooked and cooled, add to the bowl with the salad and mix together gently. When the chicken is cooked and you are ready to serve, add the @wild rocket{40%g} and half the coriander and mix everything together until the leaves are evenly coated and everything is well combined.

Share the salad between your bowls and top with the cooked chicken. Snip the corner off the @sriracha sauce{1%sachet} and drizzle over the chicken.

> Be careful it's spicy!

Finish with a sprinkle of remaining chopped coriander. Enjoy!